---
/**
 * lsm-compaction-deep-dive · Figure 4 — Level 3 "Leveled (LCS)": L0 overlapping
 * flushes, L1/L2 non-overlapping ranges (~10× each), incremental merge of one
 * table into the few it overlaps below; the SCORE box (read LOW, space LOW,
 * write HIGH).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/storage-engines/lsm-compaction-deep-dive.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). It lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the
 * MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size, stroke-width, marker-end, …).
 *
 * The source page declared its arrowhead markers (#arw / #arwA / #arwG) ONCE in a
 * hidden top-of-body <svg defs>. Because each figure is now an isolated component,
 * the #arwA (fill #7a1f12) marker this figure references via
 * marker-end="url(#arwA)" is inlined here in a local <defs> so it resolves
 * standalone (verbatim from the source defs).
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 560 210"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Leveled compaction: L0 holds overlapping memtable flushes; L1 and below keep non-overlapping key ranges so any key sits in at most one SSTable per level; each level is about ten times larger than the one above"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arwA"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#7a1f12"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text x="14" y="30" font-size="10" fill="#9a2417" font-weight="700">L0</text>
            <g fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
                ><rect x="40" y="18" width="70" height="18" rx="3"></rect><rect
                    x="90"
                    y="18"
                    width="70"
                    height="18"
                    rx="3"></rect><rect x="140" y="18" width="70" height="18" rx="3"></rect></g
            >
            <text x="320" y="31" font-size="9" fill="#9a2417"
                >overlapping — whole memtable flushes</text
            >
            <text x="14" y="66" font-size="10" fill="#1f3a5a" font-weight="700">L1</text>
            <g fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"
                ><rect x="40" y="54" width="56" height="18" rx="3"></rect><rect
                    x="100"
                    y="54"
                    width="56"
                    height="18"
                    rx="3"></rect><rect x="160" y="54" width="56" height="18" rx="3"></rect><rect
                    x="220"
                    y="54"
                    width="56"
                    height="18"
                    rx="3"></rect></g
            >
            <text x="320" y="67" font-size="9" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >non-overlapping — a key in ≤ 1 table here</text
            >
            <text x="14" y="106" font-size="10" fill="#1f3a5a" font-weight="700">L2</text>
            <g fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"
                ><rect x="40" y="94" width="40" height="18" rx="3"></rect><rect
                    x="84"
                    y="94"
                    width="40"
                    height="18"
                    rx="3"></rect><rect x="128" y="94" width="40" height="18" rx="3"></rect><rect
                    x="172"
                    y="94"
                    width="40"
                    height="18"
                    rx="3"></rect><rect x="216" y="94" width="40" height="18" rx="3"></rect><rect
                    x="260"
                    y="94"
                    width="40"
                    height="18"
                    rx="3"></rect></g
            >
            <text x="360" y="107" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f">~10× larger each level</text>
            <!-- incremental merge -->
            <line x1="120" y1="74" x2="150" y2="92" stroke="#7a1f12" marker-end="url(#arwA)"></line>
            <text x="190" y="86" font-size="8" fill="#7a1f12"
                >merge 1 table into the few it overlaps below</text
            >
            <!-- score box -->
            <rect
                x="40"
                y="128"
                width="480"
                height="62"
                rx="10"
                fill="#fbfaf2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.4"></rect>
            <text
                x="120"
                y="150"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                fill="#2f5d3a"
                font-weight="700">Read amp LOW</text
            >
            <text x="120" y="166" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >≤1 file/level + all L0</text
            >
            <text
                x="280"
                y="150"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                fill="#2f5d3a"
                font-weight="700">Space amp LOW</text
            >
            <text x="280" y="166" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >~1.1×, little duplication</text
            >
            <text
                x="440"
                y="150"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                fill="#9a2417"
                font-weight="700">Write amp HIGH</text
            >
            <text x="440" y="166" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >~T·log_T(N) = 10–30×</text
            >
            <text x="280" y="184" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >every key is rewritten many times on its way to the bottom level</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The invariant: in every level <strong>except L0</strong>, SSTables have non-overlapping key
        ranges — so any key lives in <strong>at most one</strong> SSTable per level.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
